<Author>Sazwhoo
<Content>Great Location and Helpful staff We wanted location, and we got location. We didn't want to say too near to Las Ramblas, and we got our wish, as the hotel is situated approx 5-8 minutes away depending on the speed of your walk. There are 2 supermarkets to the right as you leave the hotel, which are convenient for Lays crisps, croissants and water. When eating out we went to Las Ramblas where there are less than a handful of decent restaurants, and the best was the Port- loads there to choose from. Some a bit pricey, but the chinese was lovely and for 9-11 euros a meal it was fab. Back to the hotel, the room was lovely. Nice big double bed, flat widescreen t.v (i know its not something you wish to have on holiday but we watched bits of the Olympics), nice bathroom equipped with all essentials. Our room was located over the busy road, and unfortunately this was a bit of a let down because you could hear ambulances, police cars, etc because it really is the main road. But to get location it is good to be on, so you can't have everything. The hotel walls were quite thin (as all hotel walls are that i've ever stayed in) but that would have been fine if we had quiet neighbours. We had a european couple near to us who were loud and had no respect for others. They would talk loud, sing, and yes i'm sure you can imagine what we heard at night time. Unfortunately these people were staying here at the same time as us, if they hadn't of, we would have had an excellent stay. The hotel staff were brilliant; they showed us maps, rung a taxi for us on last day, served us estrella damm in the bar (they were bar staff too), recommended places to go, and always asked us if everything was okay. We are not ones to complain so for the sake of 4 nights we didnt moan about the traffic noise or noisy couple. Please note- ask for extra pillows, unless you like to sleep flat. 
